Class ReportsCSV

java.lang.Object
server_core.ReportsCSV
public class ReportsCSV extends Object
Utility class for handling CSV report generation and reading for parking and user activity. Reports are stored under the "reports" directory in CSV format and are named as: USERS_MM_YYYY.csv or PARKING_MM_YYYY.csv.

  • Method Details

    • saveToCSV

      public static boolean saveToCSV(String reportType, String year, String month, List<Map<String,String>> table)
      Saves a table (list of maps) into a CSV file.
      Parameters:
      reportType - Type of report (e.g., "USERS", "PARKING").
      year - Report year (e.g., "2025").
      month - Report month (e.g., "March" or "03").
      table - List of rows where each row is a map of column name to value.
      Returns:
      true if saved successfully, false otherwise.

    • loadFromCSV

      public static List<Map<String,String>> loadFromCSV(String reportType, String year, String month)
      Loads a report from a CSV file into a list of maps.
      Parameters:
      reportType - Type of report ("USERS" or "PARKING").
      year - Report year.
      month - Report month (name or 01-12).
      Returns:
      A list of rows (each as map), or null on error.

    • getReportPath

      public String getReportPath(String type, String year, String month)
      Returns the file path of a report based on its type, year, and month.
      Parameters:
      type - Report type.
      year - Year string (e.g., "2025").
      month - Month string (e.g., "03").
      Returns:
      Full relative file path to the report CSV.

    • fileExists

      public boolean fileExists(String type, String year, String month)
      Checks if a report CSV file exists for the given type, year, and month.
      Parameters:
      type - Report type ("USERS" or "PARKING").
      year - Year string.
      month - Month string.
      Returns:
      true if the report file exists, false otherwise.

    • saveLogToCsv

      public static boolean saveLogToCsv(File file, List<Map<String,String>> table)
      Saves a table (list of maps) into a specified CSV file.
      Parameters:
      file - The file to save the CSV data into.
      table - A list of rows where each row is a map of column name to value. The first row is used to determine the headers for the CSV file.
      Returns:
      true if the data is successfully saved to the file, false otherwise.
